sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as UE
    participant M as Middleware
    participant DB as SQLite buffer
    participant I as Internet
    participant B as Backend

    Note over U,B: Scenario: Internet dies mid-session, recovers later

    Note over U: Session active, level 1 in progress
    U--)M: match_started {level: 1}
    M->>DB: INSERT pending_events
    M->>B: POST /matches ✓ 201
    M->>DB: mark sent

    Note over I: 🔴 Internet connection lost

    U--)M: life_lost {laserId: 23, livesRemaining: 2}
    M->>DB: INSERT pending_events
    M->>B: POST (attempt 1)
    B-->>M: TIMEOUT (30s)
    M->>DB: attempts++, last_attempt_at=NOW
    Note over M: backoff 1s

    M->>B: POST (attempt 2)
    B-->>M: TIMEOUT
    M->>DB: attempts++
    Note over M: backoff 2s

    Note over U: Player continues playing.<br/>UE doesn't know about internet outage.<br/>Middleware works as usual, just buffers events.

    U--)M: match_completed {level: 1, score: 1920}
    M->>DB: INSERT pending_events (offline)

    U--)M: match_started {level: 2}
    M->>DB: INSERT

    U--)M: match_completed {level: 2, score: 1500}
    M->>DB: INSERT

    Note over I: ✅ Internet restored (5 minutes later)

    M->>DB: SELECT * WHERE sent_at IS NULL ORDER BY id
    Note right of DB: Returns 5 events in order:<br/>1. life_lost<br/>2. match_completed L1<br/>3. match_started L2<br/>4. match_completed L2<br/>5. (etc)

    loop For each buffered event
        M->>B: POST with Idempotency-Key
        B-->>M: 201 or 200 (OK)
        M->>DB: UPDATE sent_at=NOW
    end

    Note over U,B: All events delivered. Backend has full timeline.<br/>Order preserved via id (auto-increment).

    Note over U: Session eventually ends
    U--)M: session_ended {reason: "time_elapsed"}
    M->>DB: INSERT
    M->>B: POST /sessions/{id}/end ✓
    B->>B: Calculate rating
    B-->>M: 200 {ratingDelta}
    M->>DB: mark sent

    Note over M: All events delivered despite outage.<br/>Player got correct rating.
